{"title":"AERON/TPU Gives Us SuperLight Race Tubes with Aluminum Valves","link":"https://bikerumor.com/aeron-tpu-superlight-race-tubes-aluminum-valves/","date":1740758868000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes-box-and-tube--1536x864.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"864\" alt=\"AERON:TPU Inner Tubes box and tube\" /></p>\n<p>AERON/TPU is the latest to step deeper into the high-performance, ultra-light inner tube game. Founded by RTI Sports Group, the folks behind Ergon saddles and grips, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/aeron-tpu-inner-tubes/\">AERON</a> wants to instill longevity and durability into the hyper-lightweight tube world and swap out less user-friendly (but light) plastic valves for alloy ones.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp-scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp-scaled.webp\" alt=\"RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp-scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp-2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Their SuperLight Race series, which debuted at the UK CORE bike show, is aimed at weight-conscious riders looking for low rolling resistance, compact pack size, and top-tier puncture protection.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes-box-scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes-box-scaled.webp\" alt=\"AERON:TPU Inner Tubes box\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes-box-scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes-box-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes-box-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes-box-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes-box-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes-box-2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes-box-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Aluminum Presta Valves For the Win</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The SuperLight Race tubes come with aluminum Presta valves, delivering a lighter, stronger, and more adaptable setup for racers and performance riders.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Here’s what makes them stand out:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Removable valve core for easy sealant injection</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Better compatibility with valve extenders</li>\n\n\n\n<li>More resistant to extreme temperatures</li>\n\n\n\n<li>A machined valve stem ensures a secure pump head connection</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Built for durability (compared to plastic valves) </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp_2-scaled.webp\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"864\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp_2-1536x864.webp\" alt=\"RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp_2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp_2-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp_2-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp_2-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp_2-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp_2-2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/RoadSuperLite_Aluminium_Valve_CloseUp_2-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Weight Weenies – Prep Your Wallet</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The SuperLight Race lineup is impressively light, with models for road, MTB, and CX/gravel:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Road SuperLite Race</strong> (23-28mm, Presta 42mm): 21g</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>MTB SuperLite Race </strong>(1.7″-2.5″, Presta 42mm): 40g</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>CX/Gravel SuperLite Race</strong> (32-52mm, Presta 42mm): 30g</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> 24,95 €, £22.99, $29.95 per tube.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes--scaled.webp\" alt=\"AERON:TPU Inner Tubes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/AERONTPU-Inner-Tubes--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Availability—When Can You Get Them?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>AERON/TPU is rolling out the SuperLight Race aluminum valve tubes in April, with options in 42mm, 65mm, and 80mm valve lengths. For those looking for a more budget-friendly TPU valve version, 42mm models will be available in May and 65/80mm in July.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.aeron-tpu.com/en/tpu-inner-tube/road-bike\">www.aeron-tpu.com</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/aeron-tpu-superlight-race-tubes-aluminum-valves/\">AERON/TPU Gives Us SuperLight Race Tubes with Aluminum Valves</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"79a140f54c937402a0cbdeabeb9817d9d0ab84c5147e04fa3e765e6856d8e456","category":"Cycling"}